{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel-B HTTP MCP edge daemon, config-driven port, PURE AF_INET serve (isolation/health build). Reads edge_port_hi and edge_port_lo from its request, creates an IPv4 stream socket, binds the wildcard address on that network-order port via compose-internet-socket-address-structure, listens, and serves connections through the accept loop. Stripped to match the proven AF_UNIX edge minus the intrinsic domain/addr: no mmap of fd5 (the isolation handler uses no portal) and no SO_REUSEADDR (config-driven port makes it unnecessary), to isolate the AF_INET serve bug. Additive Channel B edge; Channel A untouched.","module_name":"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-internet-socket","package_name":"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-internet-socket","function_definitions":{"answer-model-context-protocol-requests-through-internet-socket":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"capbig","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1048576},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_hph","variabl